      <span class="sub-heading">INTERACTION WITH MONSTER CARD</span>
      <p class="paragraph">When the player lands on a monster card, they can defeat the monster using the weapon
        equipped.
        <span class="game-highlight">If the player is unarmed, their health will be compromised</span>.
        There are three categories of monsters:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Normal Monsters</b> : These are the low health monster which can be slayed easily.</li>
        <li><b>Elemental Monsters</b> : These monsters have comparatively higher health and are associatd with
          a specific elemental type.</li>
        <li><b>Dark Elemental Monsters</b> : These monsters spawns less frequently and have possess much higher health.
          <span class="game-highlight">They can only be defeated if the player's aura exceeds the monster health</span>,
          otherwise the monster will consume
          up the player's aura.
          </b>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <br><br><br>

      <span class="sub-heading">INTERACTION WITH ARTIFACT CARD</span>
      <p class="paragraph">When player lands on an artifact card, <span class="game-highlight">the effect of the
          artifact is determined by the dice value</span>.<br>
        Available artifacts:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Bomb</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_bomb.png" class="image-icon"></image> : The player takes damage if
          they land on the bomb card or any card adjacent to it.
        </li>
        <li><b>Health Potion</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_health_potion.png" class="image-icon"></image> : restores a portion
          of the player's health
        </li>
        <li><b>Poison Potion</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_poison_potion.png" class="image-icon"></image> : gradually decreases
          the player's health for the next three turns.
        </li>
        <li><b>Mixed Potion</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_mixed_potion.png" class="image-icon"></image> : acts as either a
          health potion or a poison potion.
        </li>
        <li><b>Weapon Forger</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_weapon_forger.png" class="image-icon"></image> : enchances the damage
          value of the weapon currently equipped by the player.
        </li>
        <li><b>Chaos Orb</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_chaos_orb.png" class="image-icon"></image> : shuffles all the cards
          on the grid
        </li>
        <li><b>Enema Elixir</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_enema_elixir.png" class="image-icon"></image> : buffs the player for
          the next five turns, allowing player to defeat monsters more effectively while dealing reduced damage.
        </li>
        <li><b>Mana Stone</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_mana_stone.png" class="image-icon"></image> : instantly kills all the
          monsters present adjacent to this card.
        </li>
        <li><b>Mystery Chest</b>
          <image src="/static/asset/image/artifact_mystery_chest.png" class="image-icon"></image> : contains any one of
          the artifacts mentioned above.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <br><br><br>

      <span class="sub-heading">ABOUT AURA</span>
      <p class="paragraph">The player possesses an aura attribute that
        <span class="game-highlight">ranges from a minimum of 0 to a maximum of 1000</span>. The aura value increases
        through interactions with any type of card, with the exception of encounters with dark elemental monsters,
        which results in a decrease in aura.<br>
        When the aura exceeds the threshold of 600,the player gains ability to move diagonally on the grid.
        <span class="game-highlight"> Upon reaching the maximum aura value of 1000, the player transitions
          into the Mage Realm</span>, where aura diminishes by 500 with every subsequent turns.<br><br>
        At any point during the game, <span class="game-highlight">if aura drops to 0, the player will die and game
          terminates</span>.
      </p>
      <br><br><br>

      <span class="sub-heading">ABOUT THE MAGE REALM</span>
      <p class="paragraph">In the mage realm, the player's aura decreases by 500 with each turn. The player must
        swiftly escape before the aura drops to 0 by defeating the mage.<br>
        <span class="game-highlight">The mage possesses infinte health and hence, cannot be defeated</span>. In
        each turn, the mage updates its location in grid and changes its elemental type.<br>
        When player lands on a Mage card, there is a slight chance that mage will drop the key. This will unlock one
        of the four locked doors for the subsequent five turns.<span class="game-highlight"> The player must escape
          before the door closes in order
          to win the game</span>.<br>
        If a mage is attacked with a counter-elemental weapon, the chance of obtaining the key increases.
      </p>
